{{Infobox Golf Facility | golf_facility_name = Angkor Golf Resort | image = Angkor Golf Resort Club House.jpg | caption=Club House in Angkor Golf Resort | location = Kasekam Village, Sra Nga, Krong [[Siem Reap]] 17260, [[Cambodia]] | coordinates = {{Coord|13.367619|103.816750|display=inline,title}} | establishment = 2008 | type = Resort | holes = 18 | website = www.angkor-golf.com | designer1 = Sir [[Nick Faldo]] | par1 = 72 | length1 = 7279 yards}}
'''Angkor Golf Resort''' is an 18-hole [[golf course]] located in [[Siem Reap]] province, [[Cambodia]]. Siem Reap, a resort town in northwestern Cambodia, is the gateway to the ruins of Angkor, the seat of the Khmer kingdom from the 9th–15th centuries.
== History == Angkor Golf Resort opened in December 2008 and was designed by British [[Golfer]] and former world number 1, Sir [[Nick Faldo]]. Built on former [[rice paddies]], [[Faldo]] created subtle undulations, [[water hazard]] and aggressive bunkering to create challenge but fair test for all levels of [[golfer]].
== The Clubhouse == The compact yet contemporary [[community centre|clubhouse]] offers indoor and outdoor dining, men’s and ladies changing facilities and a pro shop.
== Amenities == The club has a 300-yard [[driving range]], short game area, golf academy and [[Par (score)|par]] 3 practice hole.
== The Course == Angkor Golf Resort Yardage and [[Slope rating]] as of 2016 {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center; border:1px" ! Tee !! Yardages !! Course Rating !! Slope Index |- | Black|| 7279 || 75.5 || 134 |- | Blue || 6666 || 72.1 || 123 |- | White || 5920 || 68.2 || 113 |- | Red || 5151 || 69.7 || 116 |}
== Tournaments at Angkor Golf Resort == Angkor Golf Resort hosted the 2012 [[Handa Faldo Cambodian Classic]],<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.asiantour.com/2012/03/17/handa-faldo-cambodian-classic-2012/|title=Handa Faldo Cambodian |publisher=asiantour.com|date=March 17, 2012}}</ref> a professional tournament on the [[Asian Tour]] and is the host venue in Asia for the Ladies European Tour<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://ladieseuropeantour.com/yan-liu-wins-let-pre-qualifying-c-in-cambodia/|title=LET Prequalifying C in Cambodia |publisher=ladieseuropeantour.com|date=November 27, 2012}}</ref> LallaAicha Qualifying School. Other annual tournaments include the [http://www.faldoseriesasia.info/tic/tmtic.cgi Faldo Series Asia Cambodian Qualifier], Angkor Amateur Open and Angkor Fourball championship.
