'''''Delta 16''''' is a Finnish [[fixed shooter]] [[video game]] developed by Jyri Lehtonen and published by Amersoft in 1985.<ref>http://www.uvlist.net/game-208028-Delta+16</ref>  It was originally released in 1985 for the [[Commodore 16]] home computer and later ported to [[Commodore 64]] for which it was released free of charge. A total of 101 copies were sold.<ref>http://videogames.fi/vgfi/index.php?title=Delta_16</ref> A notable feature was an automated firing mechanism that the player could activate.<ref>[http://sinivalkoinenpelikirja.com/2013/11/22/delta-16/ Sinivalkoinen pelikirja]</ref>

