The '''Washington State Gambling Commission''' is an agency of the government of the State of [[Washington (state)|Washington]], founded in 1973 as the state's [[Gaming Control Board|gaming control board]], which is responsible for enforcing [[gambling]] laws and regulations. This organization is the second oldest national agency of such a type. The director of Washington State Gambling Commission is Rick Day, who has been the director since 2001.<ref>{{cite web|title=Washington State Gambling Commission|url=http://www.casinovendors.com/vendor/washington-state-gambling-commission/|work=Casino Vendors|accessdate=2011-05-30}}</ref>
